defs.name: Error
defs.value:
pub enum Error {

    #[doc = r" Invalid character during parsing"]
    #[doc = r""]
    #[doc =
      r" More specifically anything that is not alphanumeric is prohibited"]
    #[doc = r""]
    #[doc = r" The field is an byte offset of the character in the string."]
    InvalidCharacter(usize),

    #[doc = r" Non-numeric value where number is expected"]
    #[doc = r""]
    #[doc =
      r" This usually means that either time unit is broken into words,"]
    #[doc = r" e.g. `m sec` instead of `msec`, or just number is omitted,"]
    #[doc = r" for example `2 hours min` instead of `2 hours 1 min`"]
    #[doc = r""]
    #[doc = r" The field is an byte offset of the errorneous character"]
    #[doc = r" in the string."]
    NumberExpected(usize),

    #[doc = r" Unit in the number is not one of allowed units"]
    #[doc = r""]
    #[doc =
      r" See documentation of `parse_duration` for the list of supported"]
    #[doc = r" time units."]
    #[doc = r""]
    #[doc =
      r" The two fields are start and end (exclusive) of the slice from"]
    #[doc = r" the original string, containing errorneous value"]
    UnknownUnit(usize, usize),

    #[doc = r" The numeric value is too large"]
    #[doc = r""]
    #[doc =
      r" Usually this means value is too large to be useful. If user writes"]
    #[doc =
      r" data in subsecond units, then the maximum is about 3k years. When"]
    #[doc = r" using seconds, or larger units, the limit is even larger."]
    NumberOverflow,

    #[doc = r" The value was an empty string (or consists only whitespace)"]
    Empty,
}
